Tie-Sub version 0.09
====================

Subroutines don't have interpreted into strings.
The module ties the subroutine to a hash.
The subroutine is executed at fetch hash.
At long last this is the same, only the notation is shorter.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install

Alternatively, to install with Module::Build, you can use the following commands:

    perl Build.PL
    ./Build
    ./Build test
    ./Build install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

    Carp
    Params::Validate

